#Text=Pakistan International Airlines sacrifices goat , resumes ATR flights
#Text=Wednesday , December 21 , 2016
#Text=Images of Pakistan International Airlines sacrificing a goat went viral on Monday as the beleaguered state-run airline resumed ATR flights .
#Text=All ten ATRs in its fleet were grounded last week in the aftermath of a crash near Havelian earlier this month .
#Text=PIA ground staff ritually slaughtered the black goat beside an ATR-42 , the same type of aircraft lost in the disaster .
#Text=The move is thought to ward off bad luck in Pakistan .
#Text=The ATR-42 was the company 's first ATR back in service following the crash .
#Text=PIA said on December 15 they had chartered a Lockheed C-130 Hercules from the air force to resume cancelled services .
#Text=The crashed aircraft , from file .
#Text=Image : Asuspine .
#Text=PIA Flight 661 , an ATR-42 just under ten years old , crashed into mountainous terrain in the Abbottabad region of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa two weeks ago .
#Text=The crash killed all 47 on board and left burning wreckage strewn for several kilometres .
#Text=PIA still operate five ATR-42s and five ATR-72 s.
#Text=The Civil Aviation Authority ( CAA ) announced inspections on December 11 .
#Text=The airline expected disruption to flights to smaller airports .
#Text=Flight 661 was heading to Islamabad , having taken off from Chitral on a domestic flight .
#Text=The plane reported engine trouble and lost control before the crash .
#Text=PIA sacrificed the goat at Islamabad 's Benazir Bhutto International Airport , ahead of a successful test flight to Multan .
#Text=PIA stated ground staff acted on their own volition and were not influenced by managers .
#Text=Another PIA ATR experienced troubles ahead of takeoff on December 11 and aborted the flight .
#Text=The airline denied local media claims an engine caught fire .
#Text=Pakistani media has claimed Flight 661 was operating with some known technical faults .
#Text=The Aviation Herald reports receiving information to the contrary , and the airline also denies this .
#Text=The CAA has left decisions on returning aircraft to service at the discretion of PIA and ATR .
#Text=A CAA letter to PIA expressed concern over engine failures at the airline , and accused PIA of " shortcomings in maintenance [ and ] quality assurance . "
#Text=The latest crash is the tenth time a PIA aircraft has been written off since 2000 .
#Text=Only one other such accident was fatal , the loss of PIA Flight 688 in 2006 .
#Text=Flight 668 , a Fokker F-27 , crashed on takeoff .
#Text=The disaster killed 45 .
#Text=That accident also involved an engine failure and a loss of control .
#Text=The ATR-42 can carry up to 48 passengers .
#Text=It is a twin-engine turboprop capable of using unpaved runways .
#Text=PIA said the C-130 would be used for flights to Gilgit .
#Text=With one ATR-42 declared airworthy as of December 15
#Text=PIA also said flights to Chitral could be expected to resume soon .
#Text=A flight on December 15 using the C-130 was postponed by one day .
#Text=Please have me shifted to Islamabad where I can study and fulfil my parents ' dream — Teen who lost her family to the disaster
#Text=Chairman Azam Saigol quit on December 12 for what he said were personal reasons .
#Text=He had been drafted in to replace Nasser Jaffer following controversy generated when crews staged strikes to protest planned privatisation .
#Text=The airline loses around 12-to-15 billion rupees annually , with taxpayers making up the shortfall .
#Text=Saigol has been on PIA 's board since 2013 .
#Text=The company said it needed a chair since changing organisational structure under provisions in the Companies Ordinance of 1984 .
#Text=He became chairman in May and is a prominent industrialist nationally , heading up major organisations .
#Text=Saigol had been working for free , PIA said on December 12 ahead of his resignation .
#Text=The government has offered his job to several candidates , all of whom have turned it down .
#Text=Another issue for the airline comes in the form of a recently-submitted notice in the Senate .
#Text=Filed by the People 's Party of Pakistan , it describes an ' illegal ' sale of a PIA Airbus A-310 to a German firm .
#Text=Senator Saleem Mandviwalla said the jet had a valid certificate of airworthiness and originally went to Malta to be used in a film .
#Text=File photo of a Pakistan Air Force C-130 .
#Text=Image : Asuspine .
#Text=Mandviwalla said the plane ended up in the hands of a German museum and was sold without the PIA board 's consent .
#Text=Federal Minister Muhammad Zubair said the aircraft was sold for for 290,000 euro s despite being worth millions .
#Text=Mandviwalla has called for a criminal investigation .

#Text=In the continuing Safety Investigation Board 's investigation into Flight 661 's crash , a team of French and Canadian experts from ATR reached Islamabad on December 12 and took forensic samples from the wreck site .
#Text=The team , assisting the safety board , was also there to plan wreckage removal .
#Text=The crash site is remote , with conventional vehicular access ending several kilometres away .
#Text=Rescuers had to walk the remainder .
#Text=PIA state the aircraft was maintained in accordance with the manufacturer 's instructions , including engine changes .
#Text=The airline also say the crashed plane 's engines were inspected , as standard , ahead of its final flight .
#Text=An airline spokesperson asked journalists to refrain from speculating on the accident 's cause .
#Text=Bodies have been identified using DNA analysis , with at least sixteen returned to families .
#Text=Identification was undertaken by the Pakistan Institute of Medical Sciences ( PIMS ) .
#Text=The dead included six members of the same family , leaving behind a fourteen-year-old girl .

#Text=Haseena Gul is entitled to tens of millions of rupees ( equivalent to hundreds of thousands of euros ) in compensation and numerous people have come forward claiming to be her relatives ; she had remained with a friend in Chitral to study while her family travelled to Islamabad .
#Text=Gul is currently receiving treatment from PIMS for psychological problems .
#Text=" They will not let me study in Chitral , " she appealed to the government .
#Text=" Please have me shifted to Islamabad where I can study and fulfil my parents ' dream . "
#Text=Also on board was Junaid Jamshed , a celebrated popstar who abandoned music in favour of preaching after joining Tableeghi Jamaat .
#Text=Jamshed ran a nationally successful fashion business .
#Text=His wife joined him on the flight .
#Text=Other passengers included Osama Warraich , who was a senior civil servant in Chitral , and two infants .
#Text=On Monday , Flight 898 to Kuala Lumpur diverted to Karachi .
#Text=A replacement aircraft reached its destination over four hours late .
#Text=PIA denied media claims the original plane suffered bursts in its hydraulics , but did not clarify what had happened .
#Text=Also on Monday Flight 764 from from Jeddah to Faisalabad arrived ten hours late .
#Text=All 130 passengers had their luggage left behind ; PIA said it could take up to two days before they were reunited with their belongings .
#Text=Sister link
